In this statement, the President expresses his best wishes to those performing Hajj and celebrating Eid-ul-Adha. He highlights the significance of these rituals in reminding us of the shared roots of three major religions. The President mentions that three million Muslims, including American Muslims, will gather for prayer during Hajj. He also mentions that Muslims around the world will distribute food to the less fortunate to commemorate Abraham's sacrifice. The President is pleased that the Department of Health and Human Services has partnered with the Saudi Health Ministry to prevent the spread of H1N1 during Hajj. He sees this cooperation as an example of his administration's commitment to partnership. The President extends greetings on behalf of the American people during the Hajj season.